    opening: `Electrical stimulation acupuncture — the formal clinical name for electroacupuncture — combines the anatomical precision of needle placement with controlled electrical stimulation to amplify therapeutic effects on the nervous system, muscles, and tissues. At Integrative Health Partners, Dr. Hendry uses this modality for conditions requiring deep neuromuscular engagement: neuropathy, chronic pain, motor dysfunction, and post-surgical rehabilitation. The electrical parameters (frequency, waveform, intensity) are precisely calibrated to the neurochemical outcomes your condition requires.`,
