    howItWorks: `Prenatal acupuncture follows pregnancy-specific protocols that avoid contraindicated points (those with strong downward-moving, blood-moving, or labor-inducing effects in the first trimester). As your pregnancy progresses, the therapeutic goals shift: nausea and fatigue management in the first trimester, musculoskeletal pain and anxiety in the second, and fetal positioning, birth preparation, and labor readiness in the third. Sessions run 45–60 minutes in a comfortable, bolstered side-lying position.`,
