    opening: `Carpal tunnel syndrome (CTS) — compression of the median nerve at the wrist producing numbness, tingling, and weakness in the hand and fingers — is one of the most common upper extremity nerve entrapments. At Integrative Health Partners, acupuncture and dry needling offer a conservative, evidence-based alternative or adjunct to wrist splinting, corticosteroid injection, and surgery.`,
