    howItWorks: `Dr. Hendry's standard thyroid panel includes: TSH, free T3, free T4, reverse T3, TPO antibodies, and thyroglobulin antibodies. This panel reveals: TSH (pituitary signaling), free T3 (active thyroid hormone), free T4 (storage form), reverse T3 (functional blocker), and autoimmune activity. Results are interpreted using functional ranges (TSH optimal 1.0–2.0 mU/L; free T3 optimal upper third of range; free T4 mid-range).`,
